  "prompt": "Should people like Salman Khan (of Khan Academy) and Jimmy Wales (Wikipedia) be awarded the Nobel Prize for Peace for their contributions towards propagation of knowledge?",
  "response": "While Salman Khan of Khan Academy and Jimmy Wales of Wikipedia have made significant contributions to the propagation of knowledge, the Nobel Peace Prize typically recognizes efforts directly linked to preventing conflict and fostering peace. \n\nThe Nobel Peace Prize is awarded to individuals, organizations, or movements that have made substantial efforts to end conflict, improve relations between nations, or advance global peace and stability. Although spreading education and knowledge can promote long-term peace by fostering understanding and reducing ignorance, the Nobel Prize for Peace usually honors more direct contributions to conflict resolution and peacebuilding efforts.\n\nSalman Khan and Jimmy Wales certainly deserve recognition for their transformative impact on global education and the democratization of knowledge, potentially through other prestigious awards that specifically recognize contributions to education, technology, or social progress.",
